-- China Merchants Will Buy Nigeria Container Terminal Stake for $154 Million
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2010-11-05T15:11:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-05/china-merchants-will-buy-nigeria-container-terminal-stake-for-154-million.html
     Nov. 5 (Bloomberg) -- China Merchants Holdings International
Co . will form a joint venture that will buy a 47.5 percent stake
in a container-terminal operator in Nigeria from ZIM Integrated
Shipping Services Ltd. for $154 million.  China Merchants will initially hold 100 percent of the
venture company, with the  China-Africa Development Fund  taking
40 percent after obtaining Chinese government approval, China
Merchants said in a Hong Kong stock exchange filing today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  